         <abstract>
            <p>A systematic study of quadrature formulae for the Wiener integral ∫ F [ x ] w(dx) of the type ∫ F [ θ (u, ·) ] ν(du) is presented. The Cameron and Vladimirov quadrature formulae, which are the function space analogues of Simpson's Rule, are shown to fit into this framework. Numerical results are included.</p>
          </abstract>
